  </sponsors>
  <source>Emory University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to gather pilot data to determine feasibility of and guide the
      development of a larger clinical trial investigating the effects of topiramate as an adjunct
      to nicotine replacement therapy and behavioral counseling in smoking cessation treatment. It
      is hypothesized that topiramate will decrease nicotine craving and result in improved
      outcomes for smoking cessation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
